[{"id":42343,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/N_N9vf7uH1-JrMmrN7f6Swdy6KneJx1lMWJ9YKXs5fw.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8pWzcMcKk8sPM52C_-rDtmyC1A0L3r3Mwracf3QzVJE.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/tNpRzmgWtO62hKSYLq_rGCKn84G4-0F-GE7Mkqqk_lw.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2ZmdJLf-og46oMy63rX7b-hBc-C42X6TEBF3CJeiOYI.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/z08gsbq7w1wpcM9vyac0MGRZ7PxVmcx5mNkMIYWi34M.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\mathrm{h}=\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{gt}^2, \\quad \\mathrm{v}=-\\mathrm{gt}$ and after the collision, $\\mathrm{v}=\\mathrm{gt}$.\n(parabolic) (straight line)\nCollision is perfectly elastic then ball reaches to same height again and again with same velocity.\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/gqTIJI9AXY8oHYAZxQtovzHUqa0TQ0yiL2zJp-_tv04.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/iuFU420RP5EZkOJmxH3LHroXFfPOzesfbDjT-kJ1uQM.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2009","image":null},{"id":42201,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{v}_{\\text {avg }}=\\frac{\\mathrm{x}_1+\\mathrm{x}_2}{\\mathrm{t}_1+\\mathrm{t}_2} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\frac{50}{7}=\\frac{\\mathrm{x}+\\frac{3 \\mathrm{x}}{2}}{\\frac{\\mathrm{x}}{5}+\\frac{3 \\mathrm{x}}{2 \\mathrm{v}_2}} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\frac{50}{7}=\\frac{5 / 2}{\\frac{1}{5}+\\frac{3}{2 \\mathrm{v}_2}} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\frac{1}{5}+\\frac{3}{2 \\mathrm{v}_2}=\\frac{7}{20}\\end{aligned}$<br/>$\\begin{aligned} & \\Rightarrow \\frac{3}{2 \\mathrm{v}_2}=\\frac{7}{20}-\\frac{1}{5}=\\frac{7-4}{20} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\frac{3}{2 \\mathrm{v}_2}=\\frac{3}{20} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{v}_2=10 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (2 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42187,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["$25\\text{ m}$ and zero","$50\\text{ m}$ and zero","$100\\text{ m}$ and zero","$100\\text{ m}$ and $2.5\\text{ m/s}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"The total distance travelled by the particle is equal to the sum of the magnitudes of the areas under the velocity-time graph.<br><br>Area of the first triangle (from $t = 0$ to $t = 20\\text{ s}$) is:<br>$A_1 = \\dfrac{1}{2} \\times 20 \\times 5 = 50\\text{ m}$<br><br>Magnitude of the area of the second triangle (from $t = 20$ to $t = 40\\text{ s}$) is:<br>$|A_2| = \\left| \\dfrac{1}{2} \\times 20 \\times (-5) \\right| = 50\\text{ m}$<br><br>Total distance $= A_1 + |A_2| = 50 + 50 = 100\\text{ m}$<br><br>The total displacement is the algebraic sum of the areas under the velocity-time graph.<br><br>Total displacement $= A_1 + A_2 = 50 - 50 = 0\\text{ m}$<br><br>Average velocity is the ratio of total displacement to total time.<br><br>Average velocity $= \\dfrac{\\text{Total displacement}}{\\text{Total time}} = \\dfrac{0}{40} = 0$<br><br>Answer: $100\\text{ m}$ and zero","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (05 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42293,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Draw&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mi>t</mi></math> curve&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/37e845a3-62e5-46c6-9a2b-f895202dda50-image.png\" style=\"width: 279px; height: 208px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>tan</mi><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#247;</mo></math> above</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42322,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["10 <math><mi>m</mi></math>","9 <math><mi>m</mi></math>","<math><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi></math>","<math><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"Area enclosed by <math><mi>V</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>T</mi></math>  graph=displacement (As particle moving in same direction)<br/><br/> <math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo></math>  Displacement<br/><br/> <math><mo>∴</mo></math>  So, displacement <math><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>m</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42260,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>In both cases, the final velocity is zero. Using equation of motion for constant acceleration</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>s</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mn>27</mn></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>...</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mi>u</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>s</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>From <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math>,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mn>27</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>s</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>s</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42216,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mi>x</mi></msqrt></math></p><p>Instantaneous acceleration of the particle can be written as, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mi>x</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (01 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42303,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mfenced><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>g</mi></mfrac></mfenced></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><msqrt><mfenced><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>g</mi></mfrac></mfenced></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mfenced><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>g</mi></mfrac></mfenced></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/41e35159-84cd-44bf-aa2b-297c0969af89-image.png\" style=\"width: 183px; height: 271px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math>For upward motion of helicopter</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>s</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>h</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>h</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math>&nbsp;Now particle will start moving under gravity.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>u</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>h</mi></msqrt><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>g</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>then&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>h</mi></msqrt><mo>&#177;</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>h</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>h</mi></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math><br />&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42332,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4c720776-4d6e-4728-8a8b-ac66936f200b-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 144px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b13bcec2-6237-4a01-80dc-eb5ecb1bfa55-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 152px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/606f963e-e8c9-4ab3-99af-d7f5fb4d53eb-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 152px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dd0f457c-f401-4b28-9b05-8a18aa1b79ce-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 140px;\" />"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math><msub><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>g</mi><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>. When <math><msub><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>240</mn></math><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>s</mi></math>. So, at <math><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math> seconds first stone will reach the ground.&nbsp;<math><msub><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>g</mi><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>. Till <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>,&nbsp;<math><msub><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mi>t</mi></math>. But after&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>&nbsp;<math><msub><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math> is constant <math><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>240</mn></math>. Relative to stone <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> for (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>8)</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>&nbsp;displacements of stone <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math> ,&nbsp;<math><msub><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>240</mn></math>. And at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math> seconds stone will reach the ground. The corresponding graph of the relative position of second stone with respect to first is,&nbsp;<br /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dd0f457c-f401-4b28-9b05-8a18aa1b79ce-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 140px;\" /><br />&nbsp;","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (04 Apr)","image":null},{"id":42353,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{h} / 9$ metres from the ground","$7 \\mathrm{~h} / 9$ metres from the ground","$8 \\mathrm{~h} / 9$ metres from the ground","$17 \\mathrm{~h} / 18$ metres from the ground."],"answer":2,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":42194,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["82.5","20","62.5","92.5"],"answer":3,"solution":"During the first $2\\text{ s}$ of free fall, the paratrooper starts from rest ($u = 0$).<br>Velocity after $2\\text{ s}$ is $v_1 = u + gt = 0 + 10 \\times 2 = 20\\text{ m/s}$.<br>Distance covered during free fall is $h_1 = \\frac{1}{2}gt^2 = \\frac{1}{2} \\times 10 \\times 2^2 = 20\\text{ m}$.<br>After opening the parachute, the paratrooper decelerates at $a = -3\\text{ m/s}^2$.<br>At a height of $10\\text{ m}$ from the ground, the final velocity is $v_2 = 5\\text{ m/s}$.<br>Let $h_2$ be the distance covered during deceleration until reaching $10\\text{ m}$ height.<br>Using $v_2^2 = v_1^2 + 2ah_2$:<br>$5^2 = 20^2 + 2(-3)h_2$<br>$25 = 400 - 6h_2$<br>$6h_2 = 375$<br>$h_2 = 62.5\\text{ m}$.<br>The total height of the airplane is the sum of the free fall distance, the deceleration distance, and the remaining height from the ground.<br>$H = h_1 + h_2 + 10 = 20 + 62.5 + 10 = 92.5\\text{ m}$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42195,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["$4 \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}+3 \\hat{\\mathrm{j}}+5 \\hat{\\mathrm{k}}$","$3 \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}+4 \\hat{\\mathrm{j}}+5 \\hat{\\mathrm{k}}$","$3 \\hat{i}+4 \\hat{j}-5 \\hat{k}$","$3 \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}+4 \\hat{\\mathrm{j}}+\\sqrt{5} \\hat{\\mathrm{k}}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{a}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{B}}{2} \\hat{\\mathrm{k}}=3 \\hat{\\mathrm{k}}, \\mathrm{t}=\\frac{5}{3} \\mathrm{~s} \\\\ & \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{u}}=3 \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}+4 \\hat{\\mathrm{j}} \\\\ & \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{v}}=\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{u}}+\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{a}} \\mathrm{t}=3 \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}+4 \\hat{\\mathrm{j}}+5 \\hat{\\mathrm{k}}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (8 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42306,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6501df47-b3da-4507-a3dc-e16968749785-image.png\" style=\"width: 192px; height: 153px;\" /></p><p>Distance = Area of |v| &ndash; t graph&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (04 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42256,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>19</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>If a cadet receives the mango, then the time taken by the mango to fall and the cadet to reach there should be equal.</p><p>Time taken by mango to fall&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>19</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math></p><p>Therefore, the distance of the cadet from the tree will be,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mi>t</mi></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>18</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42245,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["A- II B-IV, C-III, D-I","A- I. B-II, C-III, D-IV","A- II B-III, C-IV, D-I","A- I, B-III. C-IV, D-II"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>(A) Here, the slope&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;always increasing, and we know that the&nbsp;derivative graph of the parabola is straight line, so the graph of velocity-time&nbsp;is straight line with increasing slope.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>I</mi><mi>I</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>(B) Here, the slope&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>and</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>at</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mo>&#8734;</mo><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. As the slope is decreasing with time, so the graph of velocity-time will have negative velocity and positive slope.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>I</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>(C) Here, the slope&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mstyle></mfrac><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>for</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>first</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>half</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>and</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>dx</mi></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>dt</mi></mstyle></mfrac><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>for</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>second</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>half</mi></math>.</p><p>As the slope of displacement-time is&nbsp;positive constant in first half and negative constant in second half, so the velocity will be uniform positive and uniform negative value.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>I</mi><mi>I</mi><mi>I</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>(D) Here, the slope&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>constant</mi></math>.</p><p>As the slope of displacement-time is&nbsp;positive constant, so the velocity will be uniform positive value.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>I</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42318,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<math><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math><mi>x</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math><br />velocity <math><mi>v</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>c</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br />Acceleration <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>v</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi><mi>c</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>acceleration</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math><br /><math><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><mo>&#8756;</mo></math> velocity when <math><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42211,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["40","80","30","70"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} \\text { Average speed } & =\\frac{\\text { total distance }}{\\text { time taken }} \\\\ & =\\frac{\\frac{80 \\times \\mathrm{t}}{2}+80 \\times 3 \\mathrm{t}}{4 \\mathrm{t}}=70 \\mathrm{~km} / \\mathrm{hr} .\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (06 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42225,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>32</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>When the bullet just enters the target, its equation of motion is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>S</mi><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Equation (1) implies that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>u</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>…</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>When the bullet stops inside the target, its equation of motion can be written as</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>u</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Equation (3) implies that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>4</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Dividing equation (2) by equation (4), we have</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>16</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mn>32</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p>Hence, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>32</mn></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (27 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42336,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1FEOVPPUFzrmAcxCLhQCJDwI484Wf3xJJ5x7HfEkpDU.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/olIleHC0Tu43GdoiLYC9gFOe210c40k5EcHNCMky0ZQ.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/utL86ZG4W2QftWJfLqghzZCPW9YLkzh-DGdxWMCqcb4.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/kqu5m0XivzUOTXVgbAcXHJ71br8XQCnOExk5tUNliiA.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":1,"solution":"Graph (b) correctly depicts the acceleration-time graph of the block.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (25 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":42334,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["$37 \\mathrm{~s}$","$27 \\mathrm{~s}$","$24 \\mathrm{~s}$","$45 \\mathrm{~s}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Person's speed walking only is $\\frac{1}{60} \\frac{\\text { \"escalator\" }}{\\text { second }}$\nStanding the escalator without walking the\nspeed is $\\frac{1}{40} \\frac{\\text { \"escalator\" }}{\\text { second }}$\nWalking with the escalator going, the speed add.\nSo, the person's speed is $\\frac{1}{60}+\\frac{1}{40}=\\frac{15}{120}$\n$\\frac{\\text { \"escalator\" }}{\\text { second }}$\nSo, the time to go up the escalator (\"seconds per escalator\") is\n\n$$\nt=\\frac{120}{5}=24 \\text { second }\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (12 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":42272,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>:</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>:</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>3</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Net force while going upward will be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>60</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Similarly,&nbsp;Net force while going downward&nbsp;will be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>40</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Since&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow></msub><msup><msub><mi>t</mi><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow></msub><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></msub><msup><msub><mi>t</mi><mi>d</mi></msub><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>t</mi><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mi>t</mi><mi>d</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42210,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{x}^2=1+\\mathrm{t}^2 \\\\ & 2 \\mathrm{x} \\frac{\\mathrm{dx}}{\\mathrm{dt}}=2 \\mathrm{t} \\\\ & \\mathrm{xv}=\\mathrm{t} \\\\ & \\mathrm{x} \\frac{\\mathrm{dv}}{\\mathrm{dt}}+\\mathrm{v} \\frac{\\mathrm{dx}}{\\mathrm{dt}}=1 \\\\ & \\mathrm{x} \\cdot \\mathrm{a}+\\mathrm{v}^2=1 \\\\ & \\mathrm{a}=\\frac{1-\\mathrm{v}^2}{\\mathrm{x}}=\\frac{1-\\mathrm{t}^2 / \\mathrm{x}^2}{\\mathrm{x}} \\\\ & \\mathrm{a}=\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{x}^3}=\\mathrm{x}^{-3}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (06 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42290,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math> from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><msqrt><mn>85</mn></msqrt><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math> from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math> from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math> from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Given :<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>t</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mrow><mi>at</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math> Angle made by direction of motion of mosquito will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>11</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;(from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis)&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><msqrt><mn>117</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>11</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;(from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis)&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><msqrt><mn>85</mn></msqrt><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>11</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;(from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>-axis)&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><msqrt><mn>40</mn></msqrt><mn>9</mn></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (16 Mar Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42324,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["$337.5 \\mathrm{~m}$ and $25 \\mathrm{~s}$","$225.5 \\mathrm{~m}$ and $10 \\mathrm{~s}$","$112.5 \\mathrm{~m}$ and $22.5 \\mathrm{~s}$","$112.5 \\mathrm{~m}$ and $15 \\mathrm{~s}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Using equation, $a=\\frac{v-u}{t}$ and\n$$\nS=u t+\\frac{1}{2} a t^2\n$$\nDistance travelled by car in $15 \\mathrm{sec}$\n$=\\frac{1}{2} \\frac{(45)}{15}(15)^2$\n$=\\frac{675}{2} \\mathrm{~m}$\nDistance traveled by scooter in 15 seconds $=30 \\times 15=450(\\because$ distance $=$ speed $\\times$ time $)$ Difference between distance travelled by car and scooter in $15 \\mathrm{sec}, 450-337.5=112.5 \\mathrm{~m}$ Let car catches scooter in time t;\n$\\frac{675}{2}+45(t-15)=30 t$\n$337.5+45 \\mathrm{t}-675=30 \\mathrm{t}$\n$\\Rightarrow \\quad 15 \\mathrm{t}=337.5$\n$\\Rightarrow \\quad \\mathrm{t}=22.5 \\mathrm{sec}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 1 Online)","image":null},{"id":42243,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Average speed in this case is given by,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>15</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42276,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>94</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>35</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e3e59396-92e9-44dd-9604-45b784062c04-image.png\" style=\"width: 281px; height: 201px;\" /></p><p>For first drop.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>2</mn><mtext>nd&#160;</mtext></msup></math> drop</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>n</mi><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>so height of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">2</mi><mrow><mi>nd</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msup></math> drop</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>35</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42209,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["$\\sqrt{t_1 t_2}$","$\\sqrt{t_1+t_2}$","$\\sqrt{t_1-t_2}$","$\\sqrt{\\frac{t_1}{t_2}}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{t}_1=\\frac{\\mathrm{u}+\\sqrt{\\mathrm{u}^2+2 \\mathrm{gh}}}{\\mathrm{g}} \\\\ & \\mathrm{t}_2=\\frac{-\\mathrm{u}+\\sqrt{\\mathrm{u}^2+2 \\mathrm{gh}}}{\\mathrm{g}} \\\\ & \\mathrm{t}=\\frac{\\sqrt{2 \\mathrm{gh}}}{\\mathrm{g}} \\\\ & \\mathrm{t}_1 \\mathrm{t}_2=\\frac{\\left(\\mathrm{u}^2+2 \\mathrm{gh}\\right)-\\mathrm{u}^2}{\\mathrm{~g}^2}=\\frac{2 \\mathrm{gh}}{\\mathrm{g}^2}=\\mathrm{t}^2 \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{t}=\\sqrt{\\mathrm{t}_1 \\mathrm{t}_2}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (06 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42198,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["the acceleration of the particle is $2 \\mathrm{c}_0$","the acceleration of the particle is $2\\mathrm{~c}$","the initial velocity of the particle is $4\\mathrm{~c}$","the acceleration of the particle is $2\\left(c+c_0\\right)$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{v}=\\frac{\\mathrm{dx}}{\\mathrm{dt}}=2 \\mathrm{tC}_0+2 \\mathrm{C}(\\mathrm{t}-2) \\\\ & \\mathrm{a}=\\frac{\\mathrm{dv}}{\\mathrm{dt}}=2 \\mathrm{C}_0+2 \\mathrm{C}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42265,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["circular","helical","parabolic","eliptical"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Clearly,&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math></p><p>Hence, the path covered by particle is a circle.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42189,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In One Dimension","question":"","options":["$18$","$28$","$38$","$48$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Velocity of car A, $v_A = 100$ km/h<br><br>Velocity of car B, $v_B = 80$ km/h<br><br>Velocity of the stone relative to car B is $v$. The velocity of the stone relative to the ground is $v_S = v_B + v = 80 + v$.<br><br>The velocity of the stone relative to car A is $v_{S/A} = v_S - v_A = (80 + v) - 100 = v - 20$.<br><br>The stone hits car A with a relative speed of $5$ m/s. Converting this speed to km/h:<br><br>$v_{S/A} = 5 \\times \\dfrac{18}{5} = 18$ km/h<br><br>Equating the relative speeds:<br><br>$v - 20 = 18 \\Rightarrow v = 38$ km/h<br><br>Answer: $38$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (04 April Shift 2)","image":null}]